From the INITIAL LINE is associated an orthonormal reference system E0
defined by the first vertex P01 P02 P03 of lines L1 L2 L3
.P01 is the origin
.P01-P02 define the first  vector E1
.P01-P03 define the second vector E2, thus
 E3 = E1 PRODUIT VECTORIEL E2
 E2 = E3 PRODUIT VECTORIEL E1
Norm(E1)=Norm(E2)=Norm(E3)=1

The CONSTANT EDGE NUMBER of LINES L1 L2 L3 define the displacement number

For every displacement i, an orthonormal reference system Ei is defined
in a same way.
The DISPLACEMENT of the GENERIC LINE is the MAPPING from E0 to Ei

The vertices from 2 consecutive lines are joined to define quadrangles.

Example: S14.1; I; 14; LIGNE_INITIALE; 1; L1; L2; L3;
        {the 3 lines of vertices define the reference system}
